â€¦arrest operator, two other suspects The police in Ogun have uncovered a suspected baby factory in the Imedu Olorvernment area of the state. The illegal baby factory was discovered when one of the inmates, who escaped from the home reported at Mowe Police Station that she was lured into the home and held captive for some time. She stated that the owner of the illegal home, one Florence Ogbonna, who lured her into the home, had a contract with some able-bodied men to sleep with them and impregnate them, adding that immediately any of them gave birth the baby would be taken away from them by Ogbonna to an unknown place. Following her report, the Divisional Police Officer, Mowe Division, Superintendent Marvis Jayeola, mobilised detectives to the scene, where 12 ladies between the ages of 20 and 25years, including six of them who were heavily pregnant, were rescued. The state Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, said three suspects, namely, Florence Ogbonna, Chibuke Akabueze, and Chibuzor Okafor had been arrested in connection with the case. Meanwhile, the state Commissioner of Police, Kenneth Ebrimson, has ordered the immediate transfer of the suspects to the Anti-Human Trafficking and Child Labour Unit of the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department for discreet investigation. He equally directed thation. He equally directed that the victims be kept in safe and protective custody, pending their reunion with their respective families. 